// @check
// @error An i32-keyed Set isn't supported yet
// DIAGNOSTIC (B6a, BUG 3): only `string`-keyed Map/Set is supported. An i32-keyed
// `{[i32]: boolean}` is the native list/array path, so `Set()` there used to
// silently become an array-of-boolean and confuse with a later "Unknown property
// add". The type checker now reports the i32-key limitation directly (full
// i32-key Map/Set support is a deliberate follow-up: i32 keys use `T[]`).
let s: {[i32]: boolean} = Set()
